## Ingredients

- [ ] ~2-4 Garlic Cloves, grated or very finely diced to a paste
- [ ] ~2-4 Tbsp butter
- [ ] ~2 Tbsp Extra-virgin Olive Oil
- [ ] 1/2 tsp kosher salt
- [ ] Bread Loaf
- [ ] ~3 Tbsp Cheese, grated

## Recipe

1. Position rack in middle to upper third of the oven. Preheat to 400F
1. Combine everything except for the cheese in a microwave safe bowl and microwave until liquid (1 min + ~15s intervals)
1. Spread evenly on each half and top with cheese
1. Bake for 10-15 min until golden and crispy

  1. Then turn up to a broil for a few minutes to finish
1. Slice and serve

## Notes

1. [Extra Tips](https://www.budgetbytes.com/garlic-bread) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20251225215131/https://www.budgetbytes.com/garlic-bread/))
